</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   HE RISES VICTORIOUS. (Repeat Assembly)

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           Am             G            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. How wonderful is the mercy of your grace!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">          C                             Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   How boundless the tenderness of your love.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 G                       Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   To ransom a slave you sacrificed your Son!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       F               E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Without the sin of Adam,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">     F                      E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Christ would not have redeemed us.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. O HAPPY FAULT
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   WHICH DESERVED SO GREAT A SAVIOR,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   O HAPPY FAULT!   (Repeat Assembly)

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am        G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. O night truly blessed
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   which knew the hour in which Christ was risen!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   O night truly blessed
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   which despoiled the Egyptians to make Israel wealthy!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           G                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   O night which conquers evil, washing guilt away!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   O night truly glorious
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            F                E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   which rejoins man to his God

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. THIS IS THE NIGHT
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   IN WHICH CHRIST
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   HAS DESTROYED DEATH 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   AND FROM THE DEAD,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   HE RISES VICTORIOUS.  (Repeat Assembly)

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                              G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. In this night receive, heavenly Father,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am               C
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the sacrifice of praise that the Church is offering you
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   by the hands of her ministers,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                 G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the solemn liturgy of the candle,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   sign of the new light.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       F           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   We pray you, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Am                              G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   that this candle, offered in honor of your name,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   may shine undimmed!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                         G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Let it come up to you like fragrant perfume,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Let it mingle with the stars of heaven.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                                G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   May the morning star find this flame still burning,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 F               E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   that morning star that never sets.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">     Am                             G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Christ your Son, risen from the dead,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                    F                      E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   makes his clear light shine, His light shine!

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am      G   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. AMEN, AMEN, AMEN! (2x)

